latestIgtvVideos.title: INNISFREE
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
*KINDLY TILT YOUR SCREEN*

Clay masks work well to draw out the oil, but they should only be worn for 15 minutes and no more than three times a week. They're more effective if you don't let them dry completely. It exfoliates the dead skin cells and smoothen outs the skin. It tightens pores and controls sebum production sebum while gently exfoliating to remove blackheads. This volcanic clay mask from @innisfreeofficial @innisfreeindia deeply cleanses the skin leaving it with a cooling effect and a softer, brighter and firm looking skin.

My skin type: Oily
Packaging: Comes in a solid tin jar.
Fragrance: There isn’t any dominating or heavy fragrance.
Experience: Overall good for my skin.

Clay masks are no doubt great for oily skin. I understand that nobody has time for a homemade face mask but I feel, this Innisfree Clay Mask is just perfect as it has 10 in 1 power.

latestIgtvVideos.title: ‘ME TIME’
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
When I was 5 years old, my mother always told me that happiness was the key to life. When I went to school, they asked me what I wanted to be when I grew up. I wrote down ‘happy’. They told me I didn’t understand the assignment, and I told them they didn’t understand life. It's okay to take time for yourself. We give so much of ourselves to others and we need to be fueled both physically and mentally. Do not let a day go by without taking some time for yourself - some time you spend in pure pleasure, as you see it. Your time is limited, so don't waste it living someone else's life. It took me a long time not to judge myself through someone else's eyes. Be The Peace You Wish To See In The World!💗
.
Video credits: @happy_clickzz 🎞
.

Swipe left‼️This man, Tabrez Shareef +919980340774 currently residing in Markunda, Bidar (Karnataka) and working in Hyderabad, has crossed all limits. He apologized this morning at 7:26 AM, admitting to harassing innocent girls, and even agreed to withdraw the FIR. But what did he do next? He unsent all his messages, trying to erase his own confession.

And if that wasn’t enough, by 12 PM, he resumed his disgusting behavior, this time threatening @mdalimirajkar and boasting about being back in Mumbai for the third time, even after multiple warnings from police and cybercrime authorities.

This man has clearly no fear of the law and has openly challenged the system, saying he will not stop. Let me be VERY clear: neither will we.

We made the mistake of showing pity last time. That won’t happen again. This man is a threat, not just to me, but to 30+ other girls who’ve come forward with similar experiences. I refuse to stay silent, and I’m moving forward legally, with full police support and security.

This post is not just to share my story — it’s a warning.
To every woman: stay alert.
To the authorities: act now.
To him: you will face consequences, no matter where you hide — Mumbai, Hyderabad, or Karnataka. We are not backing off.

Let this be a message to every predator who thinks they can get away with harassment, you won’t.
We are DONE being silent. Justice will be served.
